<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Apple suffered several hours of widespread outages across their systems on Tuesday night, affecting iCloud, the App Store and Apple TV, among other services.</p>

<p>It was not clear what was causing the disruption, first reported around 8pm EST on Tuesday. </p>

<p>By around 11pm, the problems appeared to have been fixed. </p>

<p>Apple's dashboard, showing the status of their services, was alight during the three hour window with red warning signs, indicating outages.</p>

<p>Apple's dashboard on Tuesday was showing outages across the system </p>

<p>Apple TV, Apple Arcade, Apple Books, Apple TV, iCloud and iTunes were just some of the services affected.</p>

<p>On the site, Apple said: 'Users are experiencing a problem with this service. We are investigating and will update the status as more information becomes available.' </p>

<p>Apple is not the only company to experience services outages lately.</p>

<p>Many Microsoft services were affected by a multi-hour outage on Monday, and there was a multi-state 911 outage on Monday as well. </p>

<p>By 11pm EST on Tuesday all of Apple's systems were back to their normal operations</p>

<p>The App Store was among the services which was down on Tuesday night's outage</p>
